        <h2 style="font-size: 2em;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 0 18px;">
         What are the common signs and symptoms of PCOD problem / PCOS?</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2em;
    margin: 0;
    font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
    padding: 0 0 20px;"> 
      Some females start seeing symptoms around the time of their first period, some women only discover when they have gained a lot of weight or trouble getting pregnant. The most common signs and symptoms of PCOD Problem or PCOS in females are:<br />
         1. Irregular menstruation (Oligomenorrhea)<br />
         2. Skipped or absence of menstruation (Amenorrhea)<br />   
         3. Heavy menstrual bleeding (Menorrhagia)<br />
         4. Excessive Hair growth (face, body - including on back, belly, and chest)<br />
         5. Acne (face, chest, and upper back)<br />
         6. Weight gain<br />
         7. Hair loss (hair on the scalp gets thinner and fall out)<br />
         8. Skin darkening (Neck, in the groin, and under the breasts)
    </p>
